 {"id":"git_safety_guard-ksk.2.3","title":"Tests: ensure exact behavior parity for regex swap","description":"Run golden corpus tests + add targeted tests for regex engine selection.","notes":"Include explicit tests that patterns with lookahead/backref are routed to fancy-regex, and others to linear regex. Use isomorphism harness as the main guardrail.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T15:09:02.418066027-05:00","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-09T15:09:02.418066027-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"git_safety_guard-ksk.2.3","depends_on_id":"git_safety_guard-ksk.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-09T15:09:02.419702534-05:00","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"git_safety_guard-ksk.3","title":"EnabledKeywordIndex: global keyword scan + pack prefilter","description":"Build a reusable keyword index to avoid repeated per-pack scanning.","notes":"Current flow: global quick-reject scans all keywords; then each pack re-scans its own keywords in both safe + destructive passes. This duplicates work.

Goal: build an index (Aho-Corasick + keyword→pack mapping) once per enabled pack set, then for each command: (1) quick-reject if no keyword in executable spans, (2) compute candidate pack list from matches, and (3) only evaluate those packs.

Isomorphism constraints: same word-boundary semantics as pack_aware_quick_reject, same pack ordering for evaluation, and conservative behavior when keyword list is empty.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T15:09:02.451355934-05:00","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-09T15:09:02.451355934-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"git_safety_guard-ksk.3","depends_on_id":"git_safety_guard-ksk","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-09T15:09:02.452660394-05:00","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"git_safety_guard-ksk.3","depends_on_id":"git_safety_guard-ksk.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-09T15:09:13.132919782-05:00","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"git_safety_guard-ksk.3.1","title":"Design keyword index + word-boundary rules","description":"Specify data structures and exact matching semantics before coding.","notes":"Document: (a) how executable spans are derived, (b) how word-boundary is enforced, (c) mapping from matched keyword to pack candidates, and (d) fallback behavior when no keywords configured.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T15:09:02.482930365-05:00","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-09T15:09:02.482930365-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"git_safety_guard-ksk.3.1","depends_on_id":"git_safety_guard-ksk.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-09T15:09:02.484231469-05:00","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
